title: Motorcyclist Killed In Collision Near Tea
text:
Motorcyclist Killed In Collision Near Tea October 26, 2015, 9:30 AM TEA, SD - 
On Sunday, 55-year-old Bradley Carlson, of Tea, died in a two-vehicle crash near the Interstate 29 and 229 interchange. 
The South Dakota Department of Public Safety said a 2004 Chevrolet Silverado, driven by a 25-year-old Brandon man, was traveling south on I-29 just after 4:30 a.m. 
Authorities said the pickup went into the west ditch, back onto the road, into the median, and eventually rolled. A motorcycle traveling north on the interstate, driven by Carlson, crashed with the pickup. He was pronounced dead at the scene. 
The interstate was closed to traffic for about four hours Sunday morning. 
The South Dakota Highway Patrol continues to investigate.
